This generator is built using recursion. It checks if the current node is a tuple or list; if so, it processes its children by yielding all elements found in subcalls before yield-forward iteration.

```python
def get_all_elements(
    node: astroid.node_classes.NodeNG
) -> Iterable[astroid.node_classes.NodeNG]:
    """Recursively returns all atoms in nested lists and tuples."""
    if isinstance(node, (astroid.Tuple, astroid.List)):
        for child in node.elts:
            for e in get_all_elements(child):
                yield e
    else:
        yield node
```

The function correctly flattens nested collections but inherently treats any object not explicitly defined as a list or tuple as an atomic unit.

